The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Jajpur, Feb. 18 (PTI): The torso of an eight-year-old girl has been found in Orissas Jajpur district, with locals calling it a case of human sacrifice. Police said the headless body of the girl, missing from her home since February 11, was found last evening from Ichhapur near Sukinda.           
	Villagers said a tribal man from Ichhapur who was known to practise black magic was missing since the recovery of the torso.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Barack Obama called Prime Minister Manmohan Singh on Thursday and condemned Saturdays terror blast in Pune that has claimed 11 lives. In the brief telephonic conversation, Obama condoled the loss of lives, the PMO said.                  
	 Actor Nirmal Pandey, best remembered for his portrayal of dacoit Vikram Mallah in Bandit Queen, died in Mumbai on Thursday afternoon following a heart attack. He was 48. A National School of Drama graduate, Pandey acted in award-winning films like Daayra, Is Raat Ki Subah Nahin and the soon-to-be-released Lahore. A terrific actor and human being who had yet to achieve his full potential, was the tweet from Bandit Queen director Shekhar Kapur.                   
	 Srinagar (PTI): Two militants have been killed in Kashmirs Pulwama district after a four-hour gun battle. The house where the militants were hiding had to be brought down, police said. The bodies of the militants have not been recovered.                                                                                                                                              
